@startuml HardwareCabling
title Hardware cabling topology

skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

node "pve-gw" as PVEGW
node "pve-nas" as PVENAS
node "Macbook" as MAC
node "Dell Thunderbolt dock" as DOCK
node "pc-b760m" as PCB760M
node "pc-z490m" as PCZ490M

node "4 DP/HDMI IN, 2 OUT KVM\n4 computers share 2 monitors\nIN1..IN4 + OUT DP/HDMI + USB console" as KVM
node "Monitor 1\nDP1 + HDMI1 + HDMI2" as M1
node "Monitor 2\nDP1 + HDMI1 + HDMI2" as M2
node "Keyboard1 + Mouse1" as KM1

PVEGW --> KVM : HDMI -> IN1 HDMI1\nUSB -> IN1 USB1
PVENAS --> KVM : HDMI -> IN2 HDMI2\nUSB -> IN2 USB2
MAC --> DOCK : Thunderbolt
DOCK --> KVM : DP -> IN3 DP3\nHDMI -> IN3 HDMI3\nUSB -> IN3 USB3
PCB760M --> KVM : DP -> IN4 DP4\nHDMI -> IN4 HDMI4\nUSB -> IN4 USB4

KM1 --> KVM : shared keyboard/mouse
KVM --> M1 : OUT DP1 -> DP1
KVM --> M2 : OUT HDMI1 -> HDMI2

PCZ490M --> M2 : video -> direct input\n(HDMI1 or DP1 pending verification)

note right of PCZ490M
The exact pc-z490m monitor input is pending verification.
The stable topology is pc-z490m bypassing KVM
and using only Monitor 2.
end note

@enduml
